This place was closed for a while for renovations but did they change owners too?! This used to be one of my favorite local haunts, now I won't be recommending nor going here again.  My experience there last night was atrocious. Host seating us was fine but it went down hill quickly from there. Menu changed where it is more condensed and they took out a bunch of things like the tadek topped with sabzi app and such. The two apps and two kabob entrees we ordered was all bland and lackluster.  Our waiter could seriously care less about actually being a waiter, like dude, why are you even doing this job if you're so uninterested??? As we were ordering he showed zero signs that he even heard us and made zero eye contact. It was the oddest experience ever. The really weird thing was that we were being served completely differently than the customers who were Persian/middle eastern decent. I didn't notice until my dinner date, who had never been there before, pointed it out. Our portions were way smaller, they just put down wheat pita on the table without asking if we wanted that. Never once checked on us to see how things were. It got to the point I had to rudely snap my fingers at the waiter to just get more water.  I always felt I got more than my money's worth here but sadly last night's meal proved otherwise. Will not be returning.
